ne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":25,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Praers was born in 1265, in Nantwich, Cheshire, England, his father, Baron Robert de Praers, was 36 and his mother, Ellen de Rode, was 62. He married Sibyl de Crewe about 1283. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. He died in 1295, in Somme, Picardie, France, at the age of 30."},"et":{"1265–1295":"1265–1295","1270–1296":"1270–1296","1281–1349":"1281–1349","1288–1349":"1288–1349","1295–Female":"1295–Surnud","1296–Female":"1296–Surnud","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1204–Female":"1204–Surnud","1349":"1349","Abt 1283":"umbes 1283","1204":"1204","1288":"1288","1265":"1265","from 1281":"1281","1230":"1230","1296":"1296","1295":"1295","1281":"1281","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","Barthomley, Cheshire, England":"Barthomley, Cheshire, England","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Baddiley, Cheshire East, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire East, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Nantwich, Cheshire, England":"Nantwich, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"1265–1295":"1265–1295","1270–1296":"1270–1296","1281–1349":"1281–1349","1288–1349":"1288–1349","1295–Female":"1295–Kuollut","1296–Female":"1296–Kuollut","1230–Male":"1230–Kuollut","1204–Female":"1204–Kuollut","1349":"1349","Abt 1283":"noin 1283","1204":"1204","1288":"1288","1265":"1265","from 1281":"1281","1230":"1230","1296":"1296","1295":"1295","128